page.title: 05Ecology north: FINTRY
page.content: Area dominated by{Stronend,}basalt cliffs, base-rich grassland with acid moorland above 400m. Rich deciduous woodland on lower slopes at{Culcreuch {House & Craigton.}West mainly pasture with{Endrick Water}in SW, some birch woodland. {Sites of Special Scientific Interest and{Scottish Wildlife Trust Sites: {Strondend Crags, Galbraith Woods, Craigton Woods, Double Craigs. {Double Craigs:}Rare rock plants; rock rose & kidney vetch. Animals; badger. Cliff birds; kestrel, short-eared owl. {Galbraith Woods}(deciduous): Blackcap, spotted flycatcher, great spotted woodpecker, roe deer, toothwort (rare) enchanter's nightshade. {Pinetum:}1842. Foreign conifers eg; Sierra redwood, Cilician fir. {Culcreuch House:}protected bat colony in roof space. Over 1000 pipestrelles.
